Answer:
Antipattern Detected: Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship

   Constructs Involved: Register for Conference (UC2), Validate Payment Details (UC5), the <<include>> relationship from UC2 to UC5
   Explanation: "Validate Payment Details" (UC5) is an inclusion use case that is included by only one use case ("Register for Conference" / UC2). It is not associated with any actor directly. It does not include or extend any other use case, is not extended by any use case, and has no generalization relationships. "Validate Payment Details" does not represent a complete, independently meaningful service to any actor — it is merely a decomposed substep of the registration process. This is a textbook instance of the Functional Decomposition antipattern via the include relationship.
